         <abstract>
            <p>Derivatives of fractional order, $D ^\alpha f$, have been considered extensively in the literature. However, little attention seems to have been given to finite differences of fractional order, $\Delta ^\alpha f$. In this paper, a definition of differences of arbitrary order is presented, and $\Delta ^\alpha f$ is computed for several specific functions $f$ (Table 2.1). We find that the operator $\Delta ^\alpha$ is closely related to the contour integral which defines Meijer's $G$-function. A Leibniz rule for the fractional difference of the product of two functions is discovered and used to generate series expansions involving the special functions.</p>
          </abstract>
